17:56.980 --> 18:02.300
This is the Science Fiction Radio Show, a commentary on science fiction and fantasy.

18:05.000 --> 18:06.660
And here are your hosts.

18:11.640 --> 18:16.700
This is Bill Vernon and David Cruz. Our show today continues the discussion with Philip

18:16.700 --> 18:21.620
Jose Farmer. A major incident in Farmer's career began when Venus on the half-shell,

18:21.800 --> 18:25.920
a novel written under the pseudonym Kilgore Trout, appeared in the pages of fantasy and

18:25.920 --> 18:31.500
science fiction in late 74, early 75. Of course, Kilgore Trout is the creation of author Kurt

18:31.500 --> 18:36.660
Vonnegut Jr. The character Trout is an impoverished, underappreciated science fiction writer who

18:36.660 --> 18:41.340
appears in a number of Vonnegut's novels. We asked Farmer if he identifies with Kilgore Trout.

19:25.380 --> 19:30.540
Vonnegut did not appreciate the reviews given Venus on the half-shell, either pro or con,

19:30.800 --> 19:34.240
because most of the reviewers approached the work as if Vonnegut were the author.

19:34.240 --> 19:39.020
This cost Farmer the opportunity to write another novel under the Kilgore Trout pseudonym.

20:04.720 --> 20:09.800
When I applied for permission to write The Sun of Jimmy Valentine, which I really would have loved,

20:10.480 --> 20:16.720
I could have had a lot of fun with it, he said no, which is his prerogative.

20:18.500 --> 20:22.420
We asked if The Sun of Jimmy Valentine was Kilgore Trout's one erotic novel.

20:23.920 --> 20:32.040
It was not only his one and only specifically erotic book, it was also his only non-science fiction book.

20:33.000 --> 20:37.820
Farmer obviously enjoys writing about fictional authors who in turn write about their own fictional

20:37.820 --> 20:42.540
authors and so on. Listen as he describes what writing as Kilgore Trout started.

20:43.360 --> 20:51.640
In the Venus on the half-shell, the protagonist, Simon Lagstaff, had his favorite science fiction

20:51.640 --> 20:59.580
author. Just as in Vonnegut's books, Elliot Rosewater thought that Kilgore Trout was the greatest

21:00.140 --> 21:04.540
living writer in any field. He should have been president of the US and couldn't have solved

21:04.540 --> 21:10.980
all the problems. Well anyway, in Venus on the half-shell, Simon Lagstaff liked to read the

21:10.980 --> 21:19.980
science fiction works of a fellow called Jonathan Swiss Summers the Third, and I describe his various

21:19.980 --> 21:27.000
works, their album, his entitled. But Jonathan Swiss Summers, who's a fictional author,

21:28.500 --> 21:34.960
wrote about a giant German shepherd police dog whose IQ had been raised to about 200

21:34.960 --> 21:42.560
in a laboratory and became a private detective. Now I plan eventually someday on writing a book

21:42.560 --> 21:52.660
by Ralph von Baubau, this dog under the name of Ralph von Baubau. And then maybe I'll end the

21:52.660 --> 21:59.880
cycle by having Ralph von Baubau write about a human named Vonnegut, something like that,

22:00.620 --> 22:03.240
and completing it, going right back to Vonnegut again.

22:04.400 --> 22:08.960
Farmer conceded with the extended family group called the Vold Newton family, in which many

22:08.960 --> 22:13.800
great historical and fictional characters are descended from the scarlet Pimpernel. Thus Kilgore

22:13.800 --> 22:20.100
Trout is related to Sherlock Holmes, Doc Savage, Sam Spade, and James Bond, among others. We will

22:20.100 --> 22:31.880
look into this aspect of Farmer's writing some more tomorrow. This has been the Science Fiction

22:31.880 --> 22:36.740
Radio Show, a production of the Permian Basin Science Fiction Association produced in conjunction

22:36.740 --> 22:38.900
with Odessa College in Odessa, Texas.

